<div class="row content-wrapper">
    
    <div class="content-buffer cont-buf1"></div>
    <div class="content-buffer cont-buf2"></div>
    <div class="content-buffer cont-buf3"></div>
    <div id="overview-row" class="col-md-3 wrapper-contents">
        <h3>Overview</h3>
        <p>
            All reservations for Staff travel will be on a first
            come basis in accordance to a priority system.
            Flights operate in accordance to a general schedule.
            Flights outside this general schedule will have to
            be arranged with EU.
        </p>
    </div>
    @*<img src="/images/overview.jpg" alt="arial view" width="80%"/>*@
    <div class="content-image cont-img1"></div>

    <div id="passenger-row" class="col-md-6 wrapper-contents">
        <h3>Passenger</h3>
        <p>
            Reservations can be made at the earliest 2 weeks before the departure.
            The deadline for reservations is 2 days (at noon) prior to the day of the flight.
            For a flight on Friday, the reservation must be made latest Wednesday 12 noon
            Monday and Tues must be reserved before 12.00 non on Fridays. 
            All reservations must be confirmed through the EU Flight Reservations Office at
            which the initial reservation was made. At the earliest 2 days (at noon) before 
            the day of flight and latest 1 day (at noon) before the day of flight.
        </p>
    </div>
    @*<img src="/images/passenger.jpg" alt="arial view" width="100%"/>*@
    <div class="content-image cont-img2"></div>
    <div id="other-row" class="col-md-3 wrapper-contents">
        <h3>Other</h3>
        <p>
            All passengers must produce Agency Identification and / or TAL at the Check-in desk. 
            Maximum allowance for luggage is 15 kg per passenger 
            Passengers are responsible for paying airport departure tax
        </p>
    </div>
    @*<img src="/images/other.jpg" alt="arial view" width="100%"/>*@
    <div class="content-image cont-img3"></div>
</div>
